Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
optVirtual(25.10)                                            optVirtual(25.10)

Name
       optVirtual - This command is based on the gigaOpt infrastructure and it
       provides  prototyping  capability  at several steps of the hierarchical
       flow to specify and refine the top-level timing constraints and  floor-
       plan

Syntax
       optVirtual

       [-help]

       [-outDir <dirName>]

       [-timingReports]

       This  command  is  based  on the gigaOpt infrastructure and it provides
       prototyping capability at several steps of  the  hierarchical  flow  to
       specify  and  refine the top-level timing constraints and floorplan. It
       performs, at preRoute stages, fast virtual optimization using buffering
       and driver resizing. This command updates the timing graph without mod-
       ifying the netlist. Using gigaOpt infrastructure, the command  has  the
       following capabilities:

              * Provides  a  good  QoR (AAE DC,  gigaOpt global optimizer, and
                DRV-based)

              * Run in multi-threaded mode

              * Supports masters and clones

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each optVirtual parameter. For a detailed descrip-
              tion  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man com-
              mand:  man optVirtual.

       -outDir <dirName>
              Specifies the name of the directory where  the  software  writes
              timing  reports. This parameter is used only when the -timingRe-
              ports parameter is specified

       -timingReports
              Generates timing reports that reflect virtual optimization.

